text: The southwestern bubble-nest frog, plain green bush frog, green bush frog, leaf-nesting shrub frog, or round-snout pygmy tree frog (Pseudophilautus femoralis) is a frog. It lives in the hills in the middle of Sri Lanka. Scientists have seen it between 1600 and 2135 meters above sea level. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Pseudophilautus femoralis
